{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus", "name": "Double-toothed barbet", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "bird-double-toothed-barbet-710c8bf7", "name": "Double-toothed barbet", "englishName": "Double-toothed barbet", "latinName": "Pogonornis bidentatus", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The double-toothed barbet (Pogonornis bidentatus) is a species of bird in the family Lybiidae. It is found in Angola, Benin, Burundi, Cameroon, Central African Republic, Republic of the Congo, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Ivory Coast, Equatorial Guinea, Ethiopia, Gabon, Ghana, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Kenya, Liberia, Mali, Nigeria, Rwanda, Sierra Leone, South Sudan, Tanzania, Togo, and Uganda. Within Lybius bidentatus, there are two subspecies: Lybius bidentatus bidentatus and Lybius bidentatus aequatorialis. Description and habitat Pogonornis bidentatus is a barbet with black and red coloring. Its bill is large and off-white, and the skin around its eyes is yellow. The double-toothed barbet is black on the top side of its body with a patch of white feathers on its back. Its breast is red, with a white patch on its side. Females and males have similar markings, except that females have lines of black feathers on the white side patch. Juveniles of the species are duller; their feathers are dark grey. Its song is somewhat like a cat's purr. Sometimes pairs of double-toothed barbets will sing together. Double-toothed barbets generally live in the understory of dense woodland. They occupy the edges of the woods, riparian forest, and secondary forest. Some may go into gardens and forage for fruit. The double-toothed barbet is most likely to be confused with the black-breasted barbet or the bearded barbet. In flight, it's ungraceful. Behavior and diet Pogonornis bidentatus eats fruits and insects. They search in the foliage for food, usually staying below ten meters. Of insects, they eat beetles, termites, ants, and Hemiptera, which they find in the tree bark or in clusters of leaves. Often a double-toothed barbet will capture winged ants or termites while in flight. They also eat fruits: figs, papayas, avocados, and the fruits of the umbrella tree Musanga and of Solanum. Double-toothed barbets will eat the seeds of some fruits. These barbets can be found in pairs or small family groups with helpers; lone double-toothed barbets are rare. Their territories are large. Double-toothed barbets roost communally, as all the barbets in a group roost in the same hole. Nests are made by excavating a tree, often rotting, at above two meters. Both barbets in a pair will dig out the nesting hole, and both will defend it. The entrance to the nest is circular, five or more centimeters across. Some nests have an entrance tunnel. At maximum, a nest is 46 cm deep. Breeding When a male double-toothed barbet displays for a female, he swings his tail and body around. He also shows the patches of white feathers on his flank. The courting birds will preen each other and go back and forth. The male will sometimes tap a nest entrance to attract the female toward it. Breeding happens year-round. The female lays between two and four eggs, which are white. Incubation of the eggs lasts for about 13 days. At first, adult birds feed the hatchlings insects, then later mostly fruit. The hatchlings' parents and the helpers remove feces from the nest. After 37 to 39 days, the hatchlings fledge. References", "shortSummary": "The double-toothed barbet (Pogonornis bidentatus) is a species of bird in the family Lybiidae. It is found in Angola, Benin, Burundi, Camer…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d6/Beardedbarbet.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-pogonornis", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-pogonornis", "species": "taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus"}, "expandable": true, "x": 232.33, "y": 438.95, "z": -143.63}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-pogonornis", "name": "Pogonornis", "latinName": "Pogonornis", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Pogonornis（Pogonornis）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联5种鸟类，如Brown-breasted barbet、Black-backed barbet、Double-toothed barbet等5种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 5, "x": -27.17, "y": 456.36, "z": -76.06}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus", "name": "Double-toothed barbet", "latinName": "Pogonornis bidentatus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Double-toothed barbet（Pogonornis bidentatus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Double-toothed barbet。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 232.33, "y": 438.95, "z": -135.25}], "links": [{"key": "bird-double-toothed-barbet-710c8bf7__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus", "source": "bird-double-toothed-barbet-710c8bf7", "target": "taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-pogonornis", "source": "taxonomy-species-pogonornis-bidentatus", "target": "taxonomy-genus-pogonornis", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Double-toothed barbet 属于属 Pogonornis。"}]}
